latestPosts.caption:
I think about them at night 🫨 To say I am obsessed is an understatement (Not affiliated, just a fan). @cal_snacks These little bags of sweet gold are not only ridiculously healthy, but insanely good! A bit perplexed as to how it can taste better than a sweet potato itself considering—it’s a sweet potato itself. It’s just a wrinkly, delicious lump of spud that has been added to the daily snack(s). We got these at Costco and I believe they’re just over $11. If I could buy pallets.. I probably would. I put them in my daughter’s lunch, my husband’s office, the trucks, the car, the backpacks, the travel bags, the running fanny pack, the hiking camel pacs.. I have graced Costco with my presence three times in the last four days just to go back to get these. 😋 
PS if you ever go to Costco, just bring your own tote bags and do self check out. You’ll get in and out of there in half the time 😎😎😎🤓
